1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,299
It's been great this week, hasn't it?

2
00:00:02,299 --> 00:00:05,800
And thank you to you who have prepared

3
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,000
and then sung the music.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,000
I think sometimes we're very careful to appreciate

5
00:00:13,279 --> 00:00:16,520
those who teach and preach and things like that.

6
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:19,319
And sometimes we forget that the amount of work

7
00:00:19,319 --> 00:00:22,200
that goes into preparing the music

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:24,559
that so blesses our heart.

9
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:27,399
So for all of those of you that come early

10
00:00:27,399 --> 00:00:30,760
and all of those of you that prepare through the week

11
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,880
and then present those beautiful songs to us,

12
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:34,319
they bless my heart.

13
00:00:34,319 --> 00:00:36,959
I'm grateful for that and thank you for it.

14
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:39,900
Well, let's take our Bibles tonight

15
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:43,599
and would you turn with me to Ephesians chapter three.

16
00:00:45,619 --> 00:00:47,819
Aren't you glad I didn't say Psalms?

17
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,400
I do know there's a New Testament, okay?

18
00:00:52,400 --> 00:00:55,000
Ephesians chapter three.

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Two verses as our text, verses 20 and 21.

20
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,239
There the Bible says,

21
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:10,239
"'Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly

22
00:01:11,440 --> 00:01:15,559
"'above all that we ask or think

23
00:01:15,559 --> 00:01:19,059
"'according to the power that worketh in us,

24
00:01:19,059 --> 00:01:24,059
"'unto him be glory in the church by Christ Jesus,

25
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:29,860
"'throughout all ages, world without end, amen.'"

26
00:01:31,459 --> 00:01:33,059
Let's pray.

27
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:34,699
Father, we're grateful for this evening

28
00:01:34,699 --> 00:01:35,540
that you've given us.

29
00:01:35,540 --> 00:01:37,900
We're thankful for the rain.

30
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:42,220
Lord, we appreciate the blessing of that.

31
00:01:43,099 --> 00:01:45,980
We pray now that you would speak to our hearts

32
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:48,180
as we gather together.

33
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:52,180
We're here because we do desire to know your word,

34
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:53,900
to be instructed from it.

35
00:01:54,900 --> 00:01:56,239
And Lord, we confess to you

36
00:01:56,239 --> 00:01:59,139
that we desperately need your spirit's help

37
00:01:59,139 --> 00:02:03,339
in discerning its truth and how to apply it to our lives.

38
00:02:04,339 --> 00:02:07,580
So would you use this time, minister to our hearts,

39
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:10,940
teach us, convict us where we need to be convicted,

40
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:13,059
encourage people.

41
00:02:13,059 --> 00:02:16,199
I pray in Jesus' name, amen.

42
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:21,820
When the Israelites came up out of Egypt,

43
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:24,380
they came up shouting.

44
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:27,020
They were rejoicing.

45
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:31,860
They had been crying out to the Lord for years and years

46
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:35,820
because of the bondage that they found themselves in.

47
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:39,100
Living in Egypt in the end was far different

48
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:42,179
from when they went into Egypt.

49
00:02:42,179 --> 00:02:47,179
And the taskmasters demanded great effort from all of them

50
00:02:47,419 --> 00:02:49,380
and there was great cruelty

51
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:51,820
in the effort that they demanded.

52
00:02:51,820 --> 00:02:54,100
And so when God finally worked,

53
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,220
and I shouldn't say it that way,

54
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:58,899
when God did work and the plagues were accomplished

55
00:02:58,899 --> 00:03:02,619
and Pharaoh was convinced by the mighty power of God

56
00:03:02,619 --> 00:03:05,839
to let his people, God's people go,

57
00:03:05,839 --> 00:03:07,580
it was amazing what took place

58
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:10,259
and just seemed like a moment.

59
00:03:10,259 --> 00:03:13,979
They were out of bondage and coming out

60
00:03:13,979 --> 00:03:17,500
to what they had known to be or had heard to be

61
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,580
the promised land.

62
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:22,500
Not only were they coming out free people,

63
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:25,100
but the Egyptians had been moved

64
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:28,580
to shower them with great treasures.

65
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:31,500
And they weren't coming out poor shepherds.

66
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:34,839
They were coming out with great riches

67
00:03:34,839 --> 00:03:37,899
from perhaps the wealthiest

68
00:03:37,899 --> 00:03:41,380
and most affluent kingdom on earth at that time.

69
00:03:41,380 --> 00:03:44,500
They were bringing their herds with them.

70
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,240
I've heard all kinds of estimates

71
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,199
of how many was in their number,

72
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:51,240
but I don't think it's at all an exaggeration

73
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:55,160
to say that there were at least a million people

74
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:57,440
marching up out of Egypt,

75
00:03:57,440 --> 00:03:59,839
carrying the treasures of Egypt

76
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:03,179
with all of their families and all of their flocks

77
00:04:03,179 --> 00:04:07,039
and all of their herds, and they were rejoicing.

78
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:09,080
They were following God's will

79
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:12,039
and God was leading and God was blessing.

80
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:17,040
And in God's will and by God's hand,

81
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:22,540
God marched them right down to the shores of the Red Sea.

82
00:04:25,519 --> 00:04:30,519
And all of a sudden when they are confronted with a sea,

83
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,519
and by the way, it wasn't the Reed Sea,

84
00:04:33,519 --> 00:04:37,440
it was the Red Sea, it was a real sea.

85
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,899
And there was no way, they weren't shipbuilders,

86
00:04:39,899 --> 00:04:42,820
they weren't engineers of that nature.

87
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:46,859
And when they realized that they could not go forward,

88
00:04:46,859 --> 00:04:51,859
my goodness, their joy turned to real anger.

89
00:04:52,619 --> 00:04:57,179
And sometimes when we get angry, it turns to blame.

90
00:04:57,179 --> 00:05:00,059
And these same people that had been singing

91
00:05:00,059 --> 00:05:02,880
are now crying out to Moses,

92
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:06,040
"'Because there were no graves in Egypt,

93
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:11,440
"'hast thou taken us away to die in the wilderness?

94
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,059
"'Wherefore hast thou dealt thus with us

95
00:05:14,059 --> 00:05:16,660
"'to carry us forth out of Egypt?

96
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:20,519
"'Is not this the word that we did tell thee in Egypt,

97
00:05:20,519 --> 00:05:24,820
"'saying, let us alone, that we may serve the Egyptians?

98
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:28,279
"'For it had been better for us to serve the Egyptians

99
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:31,959
"'than that we should die in this wilderness.'"

100
00:05:31,959 --> 00:05:33,519
Now can I remind you,

101
00:05:33,519 --> 00:05:36,920
that's not what they were saying in Egypt.

102
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,040
They weren't saying, oh, Moses, leave us alone.

103
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:41,760
We love it here.

104
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,920
We love the lash on our back.

105
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,760
We love being in bondage.

106
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:49,420
We love not having freedom to live our lives as we want.

107
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:53,079
They were begging to be delivered.

108
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:56,679
But now they stand at the shore of the Red Sea.

109
00:05:56,679 --> 00:05:59,839
If they turn to their right, basically to their right,

110
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:02,480
they're going to find the wilderness of Sinai,

111
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:04,160
the wilderness of sin.

112
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:06,399
God's going to eventually lead them through that.

113
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:09,600
But right now, there's no way in their own strength

114
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:13,160
and intellect they can negotiate that wilderness.

115
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,040
If they go to the left,

116
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:18,640
they're going to soon encounter a place called Migdal.

117
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:22,739
Migdal was the largest fortress of the Egyptian army

118
00:06:22,739 --> 00:06:26,440
outside of the palace of the capital city.

119
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:31,440
And bearing down upon them with great fervor and furor

120
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:34,440
is the entire Egyptian army.

121
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:38,299
And they are now using that new engine of war,

122
00:06:38,299 --> 00:06:40,359
the iron-wheeled chariot.

123
00:06:40,359 --> 00:06:45,359
And Israel begins to realize we're caught, we're trapped.

124
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:47,559
There is nothing we can do.

125
00:06:47,559 --> 00:06:48,739
We can't go forward.

126
00:06:48,739 --> 00:06:49,799
We can't go back.

127
00:06:49,799 --> 00:06:51,040
We can't go to the right.

128
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,799
We can't go to the left.

129
00:06:52,799 --> 00:06:57,799
And I love in that moment that God speaks to Moses.

130
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:01,260
Says, Moses, talk to him.

131
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:06,339
Here's what he says, fear ye not.

132
00:07:07,779 --> 00:07:12,779
Aren't you glad in the most horrific circumstances

133
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:15,700
God speaks to us and says, fear ye not.

134
00:07:16,779 --> 00:07:18,260
I've got this.

135
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:20,059
Fear ye not.

136
00:07:20,059 --> 00:07:24,700
Stand still and see the salvation of the Lord,

137
00:07:24,700 --> 00:07:27,380
which he shall show you today.

138
00:07:27,380 --> 00:07:30,299
For the Egyptians whom you have seen today,

139
00:07:30,339 --> 00:07:34,239
ye shall see them again no more.

140
00:07:35,339 --> 00:07:38,220
You see, the Israelites' great problem was this.

141
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:40,299
They were boxed in.

142
00:07:40,299 --> 00:07:42,980
And they thought their greatest problem

143
00:07:42,980 --> 00:07:45,980
was that they had the sea in front of them,

144
00:07:45,980 --> 00:07:49,100
Migdal to their left, Wilderness to their right,

145
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:52,500
the army of the Egyptians to their rear.

146
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:57,000
But their greatest handicap was that their perspective

147
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:02,000
on life was contained in the box of their own abilities.

148
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:07,320
In other words, because they could not perceive

149
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:09,239
how to get across that ocean,

150
00:08:09,239 --> 00:08:13,239
because they knew no way to go through a wilderness,

151
00:08:13,239 --> 00:08:16,959
no way to get through the army at Migdal,

152
00:08:16,959 --> 00:08:21,179
they had no clue how to vanquish

153
00:08:21,179 --> 00:08:23,279
that army coming up behind them.

154
00:08:23,279 --> 00:08:26,640
Because of that, they ascribed to the Lord,

155
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,119
well, there must not be any way.

156
00:08:29,119 --> 00:08:34,119
If we can't figure it out, there must not be any way.

157
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:38,000
And then Moses, by the direction of God,

158
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,640
raises that staff.

159
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:43,479
And you know what happens.

160
00:08:43,479 --> 00:08:45,880
That sea begins to divide.

161
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:48,179
I used to, in my heart, think that it would divide

162
00:08:48,179 --> 00:08:50,400
about, oh, 20 or 30 feet.

163
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,200
And then I read a book and got to thinking

164
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,919
about a million people with flocks and herds

165
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:56,039
going across that.

166
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:58,119
And I think that thing may have been a mile wide.

167
00:08:58,119 --> 00:08:59,919
And if God wanted it to be two miles,

168
00:08:59,919 --> 00:09:01,719
it was two miles wide.

169
00:09:01,719 --> 00:09:04,559
And in my mind, a wind comes down

170
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:07,159
and dries that seabed out.

171
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:11,280
And all of Israel and all of their possessions,

172
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:16,280
everything, crosses over on dry ground.

173
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,400
Let me stop and say this clearly.

174
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,340
Pastor, do you believe that was really true?

175
00:09:21,340 --> 00:09:23,799
Yeah, I believe that was really true.

176
00:09:23,799 --> 00:09:25,799
I believe God really did that.

177
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:29,559
And they cross over and they get to the other side

178
00:09:29,559 --> 00:09:31,820
and the Egyptian army is now on them

179
00:09:31,820 --> 00:09:34,359
and they see that gateway to the ones

180
00:09:34,359 --> 00:09:35,599
that they're pursuing.

181
00:09:35,599 --> 00:09:38,440
And they come down into that ocean

182
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:42,640
and God just closes it up.

183
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,919
I don't relish in the loss of life,

184
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:48,039
but I acknowledge the power of God.

185
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:52,340
And I'm sure over on that far seashore,

186
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:53,979
there was an Egyptian deacon.

187
00:09:54,979 --> 00:09:57,820
I mean, an Israelite deacon saying,

188
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:59,619
I thought that's what God would do.

189
00:09:59,619 --> 00:10:02,099
I kind of knew that's what God, no you didn't.

190
00:10:04,579 --> 00:10:12,819
I'm just saying to you that God is able to do what you and I cannot even conceive of him doing.

191
00:10:14,259 --> 00:10:23,539
And we need to rearrange our thinking and allow God to be God and believe that God can be God

192
00:10:24,339 --> 00:10:32,419
in our lives. Sometimes it's easier to believe that God can be God and do great things in somebody

193
00:10:32,419 --> 00:10:41,219
else's life, but God can be God and do great things in our life. Don't limit what God can do.

194
00:10:41,219 --> 00:10:44,499
Three thoughts tonight, very quickly, well I won't make that promise.

195
00:10:44,499 --> 00:10:52,499
The great possibilities of our God, the great poverty of our minds,

196
00:10:54,019 --> 00:10:59,699
and the great purpose of our lives. Here we go. Consider with me for a moment

197
00:10:59,699 --> 00:11:09,779
the great possibilities of our God. Go back to verse 20. Now unto him that is able.

198
00:11:10,739 --> 00:11:20,579
Let me shorten that. God is able. You believe that? I do. I find it comforting to say,

199
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:27,139
but can be honest with you, sometimes saying it does not translate into my life living it.

200
00:11:28,019 --> 00:11:36,019
Believing that God is able. That word able is a very interesting word. Probably you've heard it.

201
00:11:36,019 --> 00:11:45,219
It is the Greek word dunami. And I took elementary Greek almost 50 some years ago,

202
00:11:45,219 --> 00:11:49,859
and so I am a scholar. I am an expert on the ancient language. No I'm not,

203
00:11:49,859 --> 00:11:53,299
but I got a strong concordance on my computer and I love to look up words.

204
00:11:54,259 --> 00:12:00,099
And I'm told, I don't know, I'm not scholarly enough to know if it's true, but I'm told that

205
00:12:00,099 --> 00:12:06,979
word denotes great power, and we took it literally from the Greek over to our language,

206
00:12:06,979 --> 00:12:14,019
from dunami to dynamite, because it speaks of great power. If you read Mr. Strong, and I suggest

207
00:12:14,019 --> 00:12:24,259
you do sometimes, Mr. Strong says it means simply this, literally, to be possible. The word dunami

208
00:12:24,259 --> 00:12:32,739
means to be possible. I think we can understand it this way, with God to whom everything is

209
00:12:32,739 --> 00:12:42,819
possible. I think the Bible even says that. I want you to understand that we serve a supernatural

210
00:12:42,819 --> 00:12:49,860
God. Our God is not bound by the laws of nature. Our God created the laws of nature.

211
00:12:50,419 --> 00:12:57,379
And anytime God wants to suspend the laws of nature or transcend the laws of nature,

212
00:12:57,379 --> 00:13:04,899
God can make that choice. It is His prerogative, because God is a supernatural God. We,

213
00:13:04,899 --> 00:13:13,779
like the Israelites, sometimes make God natural like us. God is not natural like us. He is a

214
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:21,860
supernatural God. There was a day when God sent His angel to a young lady in Israel.

215
00:13:22,659 --> 00:13:28,899
She was a godly young lady, pure. She had a desire to be a servant of the Lord, to be used of the

216
00:13:28,899 --> 00:13:35,459
Lord, and God was going to use her. And so God came and sent the angel to her, and the angel

217
00:13:35,459 --> 00:13:43,299
said to her, Mary, you're going to have a baby. And not in a sinful, doubting way,

218
00:13:43,299 --> 00:13:48,500
but in a wonderment way, Mary says to the angel, well, you don't understand.

219
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:58,419
You see, Mr. Angel, there's a biological process whereby men become daddies and

220
00:13:58,419 --> 00:14:04,739
mommies become mommies. And I have not entered into that process, so I think maybe you found

221
00:14:04,739 --> 00:14:13,379
the wrong Mary, because it wouldn't be possible for me to have a child, because I have not been

222
00:14:13,379 --> 00:14:22,179
with man. And I love the angel. God's Word, He says back to her, the Holy Ghost shall come upon

223
00:14:22,179 --> 00:14:30,339
thee, and the power of the highest shall overshadow thee. Therefore also that holy thing

224
00:14:30,339 --> 00:14:36,820
which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of God. And behold, thy cousin Elizabeth,

225
00:14:36,820 --> 00:14:43,380
she has also conceived a son in her old age, and this is the sixth month with her, who was called

226
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:54,339
barren. For with God, nothing shall be impossible. Mary, I know you've got honest questions.

227
00:14:54,339 --> 00:15:00,260
I know there's confusion in your mind, so let me explain it to you. Here's what's going to happen.

228
00:15:00,260 --> 00:15:08,100
The Holy Ghost is going to come upon you, and the Holy Ghost is going to overshadow you.

229
00:15:08,899 --> 00:15:16,339
And because our great and supernatural God may choose to do as He pleases, the Holy Ghost is

230
00:15:16,339 --> 00:15:25,859
going to put in your womb a child. Not a child conceived by a human father, lest he have a sin

231
00:15:25,859 --> 00:15:34,419
nature, but a child conceived, if you will, in the mind of God. And God is going to place that in your

232
00:15:34,419 --> 00:15:42,979
womb. And then in an amazing process, He's going to overshadow you, and that child is going to grow

233
00:15:42,979 --> 00:15:50,979
as a child normally grows in your womb. And when you come to full term, you're going to give birth

234
00:15:50,979 --> 00:15:59,220
to a baby boy that has not got the seed of man, but is the seed of God, because He's going to save

235
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:08,500
people from their sins. And Mary said, okay. You say, preacher, we think you're pushing the limits

236
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:17,940
tonight. You got us crossing an ocean on dry ground, and now you're telling us you believe

237
00:16:17,940 --> 00:16:27,779
that a virgin can conceive and bear a son? Yes. Do you actually believe that, preacher? Yes.

238
00:16:28,419 --> 00:16:34,500
Can you explain it to me, preacher? Yes. The Holy Ghost is going to come upon her,

239
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:39,940
and going to overshadow her. And those are God's words. And by faith, I trust what God,

240
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:46,820
and only God can do. And He says to Mary, hey, just in case you wonder about the power of God,

241
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:51,940
God's going to do it that way with you. But you do remember your cousin Elizabeth up north,

242
00:16:51,940 --> 00:16:57,299
don't you? Well, God's also done something marvelous in her life. Her and her husband,

243
00:16:57,380 --> 00:17:04,979
who are both way past childbearing age. Hey, your cousin Elizabeth is with child six months,

244
00:17:05,619 --> 00:17:15,380
because God can do what God wants to do, because God is able. And you and I need to stop being so

245
00:17:15,380 --> 00:17:22,260
academic, and so intellectual, and so careful about being misunderstood or perceived,

246
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:31,220
that we limit God to what we think we can do. God is able. Do you believe that tonight?

247
00:17:32,739 --> 00:17:38,579
Can God do the miraculous in your life? Can God do the miraculous in this church?

248
00:17:39,859 --> 00:17:46,979
Can God do the miraculous in America today? Can God do the miraculous in a culture that is so

249
00:17:46,979 --> 00:17:53,540
far away from Him? And I'm simply here to remind you that sometimes we've got to remind

250
00:17:53,540 --> 00:18:01,059
ourselves about the great possibilities of our God. He is a supernatural God.

251
00:18:01,859 --> 00:18:07,540
Let's deal with this. The poverty of our minds. Again in verse 20,

252
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:19,619
Now unto Him that is able to do, to do what? Exceeding abundantly above all that we ask

253
00:18:20,660 --> 00:18:31,619
or think. God's ability and possibility are infinitely above mine. It is above my asking,

254
00:18:31,619 --> 00:18:37,219
but to be perfectly honest with you, it's above even what I can think and imagine.

255
00:18:38,739 --> 00:18:48,419
One of the goals of our lives ought to be to think like God thinks, because we will never ask

256
00:18:48,979 --> 00:18:54,900
like God wants us to ask, until we think like God wants us to think.

257
00:18:56,419 --> 00:19:00,339
Have you ever thought about in the Word of God, how many times God reveals to us

258
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:06,419
that our thinking is so different than His thinking? Think about a few thoughts,

259
00:19:06,419 --> 00:19:12,260
or about a few places. He reveals to us that there's a definite difference between His thoughts

260
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:16,900
and our own. In Isaiah 55, you don't have to turn there, I know you're familiar with these.

261
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:24,659
For my thoughts are not your thoughts. Every once in a while I'll stop and I'll say to people,

262
00:19:24,659 --> 00:19:31,619
I had an amazing realization today. And they'll say, why? And I'll say, I realized God is smarter

263
00:19:31,619 --> 00:19:41,700
than me. I have that realization many times a day, do you? God is smarter than me. His ways

264
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:50,580
are higher than my ways. His thoughts are higher than my thoughts. And I've got to acknowledge

265
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:59,539
in my life that God sees and perceives and thinks of things that are above me.

266
00:19:59,539 --> 00:20:02,499
He says this to me in James 4,

267
00:20:02,499 --> 00:20:04,999
ye lust and have not,

268
00:20:04,999 --> 00:20:08,859
ye kill and desire to have and cannot obtain,

269
00:20:08,859 --> 00:20:12,699
ye fight and war, yet ye have not because ye ask not.

270
00:20:12,699 --> 00:20:13,819
Why don't we ask?

271
00:20:13,819 --> 00:20:17,079
Will ye ask and receive not because ye ask amiss,

272
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:19,779
that ye may consume it upon your lusts?

273
00:20:21,099 --> 00:20:22,339
You know who I love?

274
00:20:23,659 --> 00:20:25,259
Me.

275
00:20:25,259 --> 00:20:26,339
I really like me.

276
00:20:27,339 --> 00:20:29,879
And I think you probably really like you.

277
00:20:31,099 --> 00:20:36,099
And sometimes I'm so myopic that I view life just from me.

278
00:20:37,939 --> 00:20:40,299
And it's all about me.

279
00:20:40,299 --> 00:20:42,299
It's all about what I think I need.

280
00:20:42,299 --> 00:20:44,099
It's all about what I think I want.

281
00:20:44,099 --> 00:20:46,299
It's all about what I think I deserve.

282
00:20:46,299 --> 00:20:47,859
And what God is saying,

283
00:20:47,859 --> 00:20:50,339
he's not saying you're a lustful man

284
00:20:50,339 --> 00:20:51,819
who's having lustful thoughts.

285
00:20:51,819 --> 00:20:56,499
He is saying you're so wrapped up in your own desires

286
00:20:56,499 --> 00:21:00,099
that you can't see beyond what you perceive.

287
00:21:00,099 --> 00:21:02,499
You can't see beyond what you can think.

288
00:21:02,499 --> 00:21:05,139
You can't see beyond what you want.

289
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:09,159
And you don't ask right because you're so prone

290
00:21:09,159 --> 00:21:12,219
to asking for just the way you see it

291
00:21:12,219 --> 00:21:13,959
and just what you want.

292
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:18,119
He says, have this confidence.

293
00:21:18,119 --> 00:21:19,939
If we have in him,

294
00:21:19,939 --> 00:21:23,219
that if we ask anything according to his will,

295
00:21:23,219 --> 00:21:25,059
he heareth us.

296
00:21:25,059 --> 00:21:27,179
And if we know that he hear us,

297
00:21:27,179 --> 00:21:28,419
whatsoever we ask,

298
00:21:28,419 --> 00:21:30,459
we know that we have the petitions

299
00:21:30,459 --> 00:21:31,999
that we've desired of him.

300
00:21:33,239 --> 00:21:34,859
Well, what a pursuit in life

301
00:21:35,979 --> 00:21:39,639
to come to the place where we understand,

302
00:21:39,639 --> 00:21:40,479
where we know,

303
00:21:40,479 --> 00:21:42,979
where we come into alignment with God's will.

304
00:21:42,979 --> 00:21:44,339
What a prayer life

305
00:21:45,619 --> 00:21:48,259
when we come into alignment with God's will.

306
00:21:48,379 --> 00:21:52,379
He challenges us to have the mind of Christ.

307
00:21:54,059 --> 00:21:55,099
Wow.

308
00:21:55,099 --> 00:21:57,979
Let this mind be in you,

309
00:21:57,979 --> 00:22:00,979
which was also in Christ Jesus.

310
00:22:01,819 --> 00:22:02,659
What is that?

311
00:22:03,979 --> 00:22:05,159
Several years ago,

312
00:22:06,699 --> 00:22:08,579
when I went to Bible college,

313
00:22:09,579 --> 00:22:11,139
I was a married student.

314
00:22:11,139 --> 00:22:12,699
There was a number of married students

315
00:22:12,699 --> 00:22:15,739
and I'm just like everybody else.

316
00:22:15,739 --> 00:22:17,259
It was just so busy.

317
00:22:17,259 --> 00:22:18,419
You would go to class.

318
00:22:18,419 --> 00:22:20,379
You would take a few minutes to study

319
00:22:20,379 --> 00:22:21,219
or go to the library.

320
00:22:21,219 --> 00:22:22,059
You'd go to work.

321
00:22:22,059 --> 00:22:23,219
You'd go home.

322
00:22:23,219 --> 00:22:24,139
You'd have an hour.

323
00:22:24,139 --> 00:22:24,979
You'd go to bed.

324
00:22:24,979 --> 00:22:26,659
You'd get up and rinse and repeat

325
00:22:26,659 --> 00:22:27,979
and do it over and over again.

326
00:22:27,979 --> 00:22:29,899
There wasn't a lot of time for fellowship.

327
00:22:29,899 --> 00:22:31,979
You just had to get it all done.

328
00:22:32,859 --> 00:22:34,019
And there were a number of us

329
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,099
that were in that boat.

330
00:22:35,099 --> 00:22:36,059
One particular,

331
00:22:36,059 --> 00:22:40,419
a man who we sat together in a number of classes.

332
00:22:40,419 --> 00:22:42,779
Our families had fellowship sometimes,

333
00:22:42,779 --> 00:22:44,219
a few times over the year,

334
00:22:44,219 --> 00:22:46,499
two, three that we were together.

335
00:22:46,499 --> 00:22:49,099
But we developed a friendship

336
00:22:49,099 --> 00:22:51,259
without a lot of fellowship.

337
00:22:51,259 --> 00:22:52,819
And when we graduated,

338
00:22:52,819 --> 00:22:54,579
he went the way of the mission field.

339
00:22:54,579 --> 00:22:57,859
I went the way of pastoral here in the States.

340
00:22:57,859 --> 00:22:59,579
And we maintained contact.

341
00:22:59,579 --> 00:23:00,939
When I started a church,

342
00:23:00,939 --> 00:23:03,819
he was one of the first two or three missionaries

343
00:23:03,819 --> 00:23:05,679
that we took on for support,

344
00:23:05,679 --> 00:23:07,419
though he did not come home

345
00:23:07,419 --> 00:23:10,459
because he was wrapped up in the work.

346
00:23:10,459 --> 00:23:14,059
He didn't take a furlough for nearly 20 years.

347
00:23:14,899 --> 00:23:15,739
He called me one day and he said,

348
00:23:15,739 --> 00:23:17,219
hey, I'm taking a furlough.

349
00:23:17,219 --> 00:23:18,459
And I thought maybe I'd come

350
00:23:18,459 --> 00:23:20,419
and show your people who I am.

351
00:23:20,419 --> 00:23:23,259
You know, you've been supporting us 20 years.

352
00:23:23,259 --> 00:23:25,379
And I said, man, when you get here,

353
00:23:25,379 --> 00:23:26,579
what a wonderful thing.

354
00:23:26,579 --> 00:23:28,099
Come to our conference.

355
00:23:28,099 --> 00:23:28,939
While you're here,

356
00:23:28,939 --> 00:23:30,519
we're gonna spend some time together.

357
00:23:30,519 --> 00:23:32,899
And you and I'll just make some time to get away.

358
00:23:32,899 --> 00:23:35,139
We're gonna just rehearse to each other

359
00:23:35,139 --> 00:23:38,099
all what God has done in 20 years.

360
00:23:38,099 --> 00:23:39,179
And so they did come

361
00:23:39,179 --> 00:23:40,699
and had a wonderful conference.

362
00:23:40,699 --> 00:23:42,499
We found time to get out to breakfast.

363
00:23:42,499 --> 00:23:45,339
And I only take people to the finest restaurants.

364
00:23:45,339 --> 00:23:46,659
And so we went to IHOP.

365
00:23:48,779 --> 00:23:50,219
And we're sitting there at IHOP

366
00:23:50,219 --> 00:23:51,699
and we're enjoying each other

367
00:23:51,699 --> 00:23:53,699
and telling each other what God has done.

368
00:23:53,699 --> 00:23:55,659
And ever seen somebody

369
00:23:55,659 --> 00:23:57,539
and you know the wheels are turning,

370
00:23:57,539 --> 00:24:00,619
but there's no connection being made?

371
00:24:00,619 --> 00:24:02,299
And I looked at him and I said,

372
00:24:02,299 --> 00:24:05,379
Jack, if you don't see anything you like here,

373
00:24:05,379 --> 00:24:07,439
we can, there's another fine restaurant

374
00:24:07,439 --> 00:24:09,819
across the street, Waffle House is right over there.

375
00:24:09,819 --> 00:24:11,419
We can go there.

376
00:24:11,419 --> 00:24:12,659
He said, no, it's not that.

377
00:24:12,659 --> 00:24:16,059
He said, I have for 20 years

378
00:24:16,059 --> 00:24:17,959
been thinking in Spanish.

379
00:24:19,099 --> 00:24:21,939
And he said, I'm struggling coming back

380
00:24:21,939 --> 00:24:24,619
and just in a couple of weeks thinking in English.

381
00:24:24,619 --> 00:24:26,599
And he said, for the life of me,

382
00:24:26,599 --> 00:24:30,959
I can't figure out what rooty tooty fresh and fruity is.

383
00:24:33,299 --> 00:24:35,579
I said, Jack, absolutely nobody knows

384
00:24:35,579 --> 00:24:37,619
what rooty tooty fresh and fruity is.

385
00:24:37,619 --> 00:24:40,379
It comes out different every time.

386
00:24:40,379 --> 00:24:43,239
But in that moment, in that moment,

387
00:24:44,619 --> 00:24:46,019
the Holy Spirit spoke to me.

388
00:24:47,219 --> 00:24:49,519
And he said, you know what your problem is, Mike?

389
00:24:50,459 --> 00:24:53,779
You have thought in Edwards for so long

390
00:24:56,159 --> 00:24:57,859
that you're gonna have to retrain yourself

391
00:24:57,859 --> 00:24:59,279
to think in Jesus.

392
00:25:00,779 --> 00:25:03,859
Now, I'm not trying to be funny or cute in that.

393
00:25:04,779 --> 00:25:07,339
I'm just saying to you that one of the pursuits

394
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:12,339
of our lives has to be to allow the Word of God

395
00:25:12,659 --> 00:25:17,659
and the Spirit of God retrain, renew,

396
00:25:17,739 --> 00:25:22,179
to be not conformed to the world, but to be transformed.

397
00:25:22,179 --> 00:25:24,019
And one of the passions,

398
00:25:24,019 --> 00:25:27,139
one of the zealous passions of our life must be,

399
00:25:27,139 --> 00:25:29,139
God, I want to see it your way.

400
00:25:29,139 --> 00:25:30,899
I want to see it your way.

401
00:25:30,899 --> 00:25:32,939
I want to see it your way.

402
00:25:32,939 --> 00:25:35,539
And not long after that revelation,

403
00:25:35,539 --> 00:25:37,539
I looked up into the face of God

404
00:25:37,539 --> 00:25:38,999
and I said something like this.

405
00:25:38,999 --> 00:25:41,419
I won't quote it, but I said something like this.

406
00:25:41,419 --> 00:25:44,259
God, how can I do that?

407
00:25:44,259 --> 00:25:46,499
I'm locked in me.

408
00:25:48,699 --> 00:25:50,819
How can I change it all?

409
00:25:50,819 --> 00:25:52,859
How can I make it think different?

410
00:25:52,859 --> 00:25:54,579
How can I see it different?

411
00:25:54,579 --> 00:25:56,299
How can I accomplish that?

412
00:25:56,299 --> 00:26:00,179
How can I get the mind of Christ in Edwards?

413
00:26:01,139 --> 00:26:03,059
And I'll tell you, God showed me something,

414
00:26:03,059 --> 00:26:04,879
and I want to show it to you tonight.

415
00:26:04,879 --> 00:26:05,739
Notice this.

416
00:26:06,679 --> 00:26:09,999
If you mark your Bible, verse 20 says this.

417
00:26:09,999 --> 00:26:13,999
Now unto him that is able.

418
00:26:13,999 --> 00:26:18,879
We've already defined that word as dunami, to be possible.

419
00:26:20,079 --> 00:26:24,999
To do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think

420
00:26:24,999 --> 00:26:28,359
according to the power.

421
00:26:29,519 --> 00:26:31,599
If you circle that word, circle it

422
00:26:31,599 --> 00:26:34,359
and draw a line back to able,

423
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:35,919
because they're the same root word.

424
00:26:35,919 --> 00:26:37,959
They're the same root word, dunami.

425
00:26:38,999 --> 00:26:41,339
Now here, I want you to notice this.

426
00:26:41,339 --> 00:26:44,119
That worketh, where?

427
00:26:45,039 --> 00:26:47,239
In us.

428
00:26:48,759 --> 00:26:50,599
God says, and I love this,

429
00:26:50,599 --> 00:26:52,439
I won't take the time to show it to you,

430
00:26:52,439 --> 00:26:55,119
but that word worketh, you're familiar with that.

431
00:26:55,119 --> 00:26:56,879
It's the Greek word intergeo.

432
00:26:56,879 --> 00:26:59,159
If we went up into James chapter five,

433
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:00,419
you would see this sentence.

434
00:27:00,419 --> 00:27:05,379
You would see the effectual fervent prayer

435
00:27:05,379 --> 00:27:07,679
of a righteous man availeth much.

436
00:27:07,679 --> 00:27:10,899
That's the same word that is translated effectual fervent.

437
00:27:10,899 --> 00:27:12,219
Here's what God is saying.

438
00:27:12,219 --> 00:27:15,979
There is an effectual fervent power.

439
00:27:15,979 --> 00:27:19,579
There is an effectual fervent possibility

440
00:27:19,579 --> 00:27:24,199
already working in you.

441
00:27:24,199 --> 00:27:26,959
It's not something I have to summon up.

442
00:27:26,959 --> 00:27:30,179
It's not something I have to make happen.

443
00:27:30,859 --> 00:27:32,979
It's something I have to surrender to.

444
00:27:39,379 --> 00:27:43,379
God help me to see that.

445
00:27:43,379 --> 00:27:46,539
It's already working in me.

446
00:27:47,439 --> 00:27:49,099
How do I have the mind of Christ,

447
00:27:49,099 --> 00:27:51,579
grit my teeth and say, I will think like Jesus.

448
00:27:51,579 --> 00:27:53,059
No, you won't.

449
00:27:53,059 --> 00:27:53,899
You can't.

450
00:27:55,059 --> 00:27:59,819
But when we got saved, back in 1975,

451
00:27:59,819 --> 00:28:02,259
84, 29, I've got some heritage people here,

452
00:28:02,259 --> 00:28:03,219
so I'll say it.

453
00:28:04,479 --> 00:28:06,019
No, I won't say it, nevermind.

454
00:28:07,459 --> 00:28:09,539
I got saved in 1975.

455
00:28:09,539 --> 00:28:11,299
I was there in the living room of my house,

456
00:28:11,299 --> 00:28:16,299
opened the Bible and called out upon the Lord to save me.

457
00:28:16,539 --> 00:28:18,059
And I'm not trying to be mystical

458
00:28:18,059 --> 00:28:19,659
and I'm not trying to be silly.

459
00:28:19,659 --> 00:28:22,659
But in that moment, man, something very,

460
00:28:22,659 --> 00:28:24,699
very important happened to me.

461
00:28:24,699 --> 00:28:26,379
I didn't realize it then.

462
00:28:26,379 --> 00:28:28,419
I didn't fully understand it then.

463
00:28:28,419 --> 00:28:30,299
I didn't fall down at foam in my mouth.

464
00:28:30,299 --> 00:28:32,940
I didn't levitate and hover over the sofa.

465
00:28:32,940 --> 00:28:35,940
I didn't have some ecstatic experience.

466
00:28:35,940 --> 00:28:40,099
But the Spirit of God, when I called upon the Lord

467
00:28:40,099 --> 00:28:43,659
and said, I am a sinner and I need you to save me,

468
00:28:43,659 --> 00:28:48,239
and he did save me, the Spirit of God pierced my chest,

469
00:28:48,239 --> 00:28:52,899
came into my heart and took up residence in my heart

470
00:28:52,899 --> 00:28:56,019
so as to make me able to become

471
00:28:56,059 --> 00:28:58,779
what Christ wants me to become,

472
00:28:58,779 --> 00:29:02,299
to think like Christ and to have the perception

473
00:29:02,299 --> 00:29:03,899
and the discernment of Christ.

474
00:29:03,899 --> 00:29:07,739
It's not instantaneous, but it is possible.

475
00:29:11,299 --> 00:29:16,219
Years ago, my wife and I moved in from the country

476
00:29:16,219 --> 00:29:18,899
and we moved back into town, if you will,

477
00:29:18,899 --> 00:29:22,179
and we had a lovely home.

478
00:29:22,179 --> 00:29:25,059
And if you don't know my wife, but if you did,

479
00:29:25,059 --> 00:29:27,459
you would know that she is a person

480
00:29:27,459 --> 00:29:30,179
that everything has to be in its place.

481
00:29:30,179 --> 00:29:32,419
And we had moved that day and somebody called

482
00:29:32,419 --> 00:29:35,019
and said, they were being very kind,

483
00:29:35,019 --> 00:29:36,619
they wanted to drop a meal off to us

484
00:29:36,619 --> 00:29:39,579
so that she didn't have to worry about cooking a meal.

485
00:29:39,579 --> 00:29:41,259
Meals are very important to me.

486
00:29:42,959 --> 00:29:46,299
And when they called and said, hey, we're 20 minutes away,

487
00:29:46,299 --> 00:29:50,799
we're dropping off a meal, there were boxes in her house

488
00:29:50,799 --> 00:29:52,940
in places that boxes shouldn't be.

489
00:29:52,940 --> 00:29:55,979
And so she said to me, we gotta straighten this place up.

490
00:29:55,979 --> 00:29:57,659
I said, we're moving.

491
00:29:57,659 --> 00:29:59,859
No, no, we have to straighten this place up.

492
00:29:59,859 --> 00:30:03,619
And so I said, okay, you straighten this floor up.

493
00:30:03,619 --> 00:30:04,739
I'm gonna go downstairs.

